sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant User as User / Client
    participant Nginx as nginx Gateway
    participant Auth as Auth Service
    participant Service as Backend Service
    participant Vault as Redis/Key Store
    participant DB as PostgreSQL (RLS)
    participant Audit as Audit Log (Immutable)

    Note over User, Auth: Phase 1: Authentication & Token Issuance
    User->>Nginx: POST /api/v1/auth/login
    Nginx->>Auth: Forward Login Credentials
    Auth->>Auth: Verify Bcrypt Hash
    Auth-->>User: Issue RS256 JWT (Access + Refresh)

    Note over User, Service: Phase 2: Gateway Validation & Routing
    User->>Nginx: API Request + Bearer <JWT>
    Nginx->>Auth: auth_request validator (Internal)
    Auth->>Auth: Validate JWT Signature & Expiry
    Auth-->>Nginx: 200 OK + X-User-ID header
    Nginx->>Service: Proxy Request + Injected X-User-ID

    Note over Service, Vault: Phase 3: Authorization & PII Protection
    Service->>Service: Authorize X-User-ID for Endpoint
    Service->>Vault: Retrieve User-Specific AES Key
    Service->>Service: AES-256-GCM Decrypt (PII Fields)
    Service->>Service: Scrub Sensitive Data from Local Logs (Sensitive Masking)
    Service->>Service: Log Non-PII Request Metadata

    Note over Service, Audit: Phase 4: Data Isolation & Audit Trail
    Service->>DB: SET LOCAL app.current_user_id = <UUID>
    Service->>DB: Execute Transaction / Query
    DB->>DB: Enforce RLS user_isolation Policy
    DB->>Audit: SQL Trigger: Write Immutable Operation Log
    Audit->>Audit: Hash Payload + Lock Row (Trigger prevents Edit/Delete)
    
    DB-->>Service: Return Result
    Service-->>User: Encrypted Response Payload
